# Wishbee-AI Development Rules

## Typography Scale
When creating new pages or components, use this exact typography scale:

- **H1 (Page Titles)**: `text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold`
- **H2 (Section Headers)**: `text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold`
- **H3 (Subsection Headers)**: `text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold`
- **H4 (Card/Component Titles)**: `text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold`

## Mobile Button Requirements
All interactive buttons on mobile must have:
- **Minimum height**: `h-12` (48px) for touch-friendly interactions
- **Touch target**: Ensure buttons are at least 44x44px for accessibility
- Example: `h-12 px-4 sm:px-6` (mobile-first responsive)

## Design System Consistency
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Follow mobile-first responsive design (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints)
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind spacing scale
- Use the existing color system from `app/globals.css`

## Component Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all new components
- Follow Next.js App Router conventions
- Use shadcn/ui components from `components/ui/`
- Keep components modular and reusable
- Add proper error handling and loading states

## API Routes
- Always validate input with Zod schemas
- Include proper error handling
- Use the admin client (`lib/supabase/admin.ts`) only in server-side API routes
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to client-side code
- Add authentication checks where appropriate

## Security
- Never use `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in "use client" files
- Always validate user authentication before database operations
- Use the regular Supabase client for user-facing operations
- Use the admin client only for webhooks and background tasks

## Code Quality
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add comments for complex logic
- Follow existing code style and patterns
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose

